## 2. The 3-LLM Execution Pipeline Flow

The core workflow of the support agent processes operator inputs using a three-phase sequential LLM setup designed to guarantee action safety, direct context-based reasoning, and RAG fallback.

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor Operator as Operator (UI Client)
    participant Flask as Flask Backend (app.py)
    participant SessionDB as Session Store (MongoDB)
    participant LLM1 as Call 1: Router LLM
    participant Tools as Parallel Tools Executor
    participant LLM2 as Call 2: Reasoner LLM (Path A/B/C)
    participant RAG as Hybrid RAG (Chroma + BM25)
    participant LLM3 as Call 3: Response LLM
    participant Formatter as Response Formatter (UI Elements)

    Operator->>Flask: POST /chat_stream (user query, session_id)
    Flask->>SessionDB: Retrieve chat history & active entities (charger, phone, etc.)
    SessionDB-->>Flask: History, cached entities
    Flask->>LLM1: System Prompt + Injected Entities + Query (openai/bedrock)
    LLM1-->>Flask: Tool Calls (e.g. troubleshoot, charger_action)
    
    rect rgb(240, 248, 255)
        note over Flask, Tools: Concurrency Worker Thread (Heartbeat to UI)
        Flask->>Tools: Execute identified tools concurrently via run_parallel()
        Tools->>Tools: Resolve inputs via charger/location resolvers (Fuzzy/Geo)
        Tools->>Tools: Call external ChargeMOD APIs (LS, TTS)
        Tools-->>Flask: Tool results (Logs, charger specs, customer profile)
    end
    
    Flask->>SessionDB: Extract & persist new entities (charger ID, verified phone)
    
    alt If troubleshoot tool successfully fetches diagnostics
        Flask->>LLM2: System Prompt + troubleshoot raw data + user query (GPT-4o-mini)
        LLM2-->>Flask: JSON Decision (Path A, B, or C)
        
        alt Path A: Direct Answer
            note over Flask: Logs directly explain fault (no RAG needed)
        else Path B: Playbook RAG
            Flask->>RAG: search_playbook(symptom, charger_type, vehicle)
            RAG->>RAG: BM25 Sparse Search + ChromaDB Dense Search
            RAG->>RAG: Cross-Encoder Reranker
            RAG-->>Flask: Top matching SOP manuals / troubleshooting steps
        else Path C: Clarify / Ask Customer
            note over Flask: Ambiguous logs -> build multi-choice clarifying questions
        end
    end

    Flask->>LLM3: Final response prompt + Injected rules (AC/DC specific) + RAG/Path Context + Tool Results
    LLM3-->>Flask: Stream final text answer (SSE)
    
    Flask->>Formatter: Build tables, action buttons (OTP, start/stop), suggestion chips, CSV downloads
    Flask-->>Operator: Emit final structured JSON via SSE
    Flask->>SessionDB: Append chat history (assistant turn, tokens, pipeline logs)
```

