## 3. Code Layer Mapping

Below is the mapping of modules and files in this repository responsible for each architectural component:

### 3.1 Web & Control Layer
- **[app.py](file:///c:/Users/admin/Desktop/New%20CSA/customersupport_AIagent/app.py)**: The main entry point. Initializes Flask, controls the 3-LLM pipeline flow (`ask_ai_web_stream`), acts as the SSE channel generator, and handles the administration, history lookup, dashboard, and authentication endpoints.
- **[auth_key.py](file:///c:/Users/admin/Desktop/New%20CSA/customersupport_AIagent/auth_key.py)**: Decodes and verifies ChargeMOD JWT cookies, returning the user authentication token and details.
- **[concurrency.py](file:///c:/Users/admin/Desktop/New%20CSA/customersupport_AIagent/concurrency.py)**: Uses Python's `ThreadPoolExecutor` to run API calls and tool processes concurrently inside `run_parallel`, reducing overall request latency.
- **[response_formatter.py](file:///c:/Users/admin/Desktop/New%20CSA/customersupport_AIagent/response_formatter.py)**: Translates the LLM-generated text block into structured JSON payload formats. Detects table formats, extracts CSV targets, and yields suggestions, buttons, and visual components.

### 3.2 AI Tool Implementations
- **[tools/schemas.py](file:///c:/Users/admin/Desktop/New%20CSA/customersupport_AIagent/tools/schemas.py)**: Declares the JSON schemas for the agent tools (`troubleshoot`, `user_details`, `charger_action`, `estimations`, `search_playbook`, `find_nearby_chargers`) in both OpenAI and Bedrock formats.
- **[tools/troubleshoot.py](file:///c:/Users/admin/Desktop/New%20CSA/customersupport_AIagent/tools/troubleshoot.py)**: Charger diagnostics tool. Queries raw logs, last transactions, active charging states, status history, and vendor error details.
- **[tools/charger_action.py](file:///c:/Users/admin/Desktop/New%20CSA/customersupport_AIagent/tools/charger_action.py)**: Action state machine wrapper. Conducts reservations, starts remote sessions (gated by OTP/mobile verification and wallet checks), and ends active sessions.
- **[tools/user_details.py](file:///c:/Users/admin/Desktop/New%20CSA/customersupport_AIagent/tools/user_details.py)**: Retrieves user profiles, wallet transactions, payment history, registration info, and EV specifications.
- **[tools/estimations.py](file:///c:/Users/admin/Desktop/New%20CSA/customersupport_AIagent/tools/estimations.py)**: Implements mathematical functions to calculate time-to-target SOC, cost, range gains, and payment/wallet sufficiency.
- **[tools/search_playbook.py](file:///c:/Users/admin/Desktop/New%20CSA/customersupport_AIagent/tools/search_playbook.py)**: Calls the RAG search pipeline or forms Path C questionnaire structures.
- **[tools/charger_resolver.py](file:///c:/Users/admin/Desktop/New%20CSA/customersupport_AIagent/tools/charger_resolver.py)** & **[tools/geo_resolver.py](file:///c:/Users/admin/Desktop/New%20CSA/customersupport_AIagent/tools/geo_resolver.py)**: Resolvers using exact matching, rapidfuzz-based substring matching, and Google Maps API coordinates to resolve user queries into canonical Charger IDs.

### 3.3 Databases & Search
- **[ChatHistory/ChatHistoryManager.py](file:///c:/Users/admin/Desktop/New%20CSA/customersupport_AIagent/ChatHistory/ChatHistoryManager.py)**: Standard MongoDB query runner that stores conversation logs, active entity caches (charger ID, user email, phone), token counts, and operator feedback.
- **[db/context_retrieval.py](file:///c:/Users/admin/Desktop/New%20CSA/customersupport_AIagent/db/context_retrieval.py)**: Performs hybrid search. Merges results from `rank-bm25` (using pickled index `bm25_index.pkl`) and `langchain_chroma` semantic dense search, then ranks results using `sentence-transformers` Cross-Encoder model.

### 3.4 Integration & External API Layer
- **[api/http_client.py](file:///c:/Users/admin/Desktop/New%20CSA/customersupport_AIagent/api/http_client.py)**: Managed request session pooling with automatic timeouts, backoffs, and retries.
- **[api/chargepoints.py](file:///c:/Users/admin/Desktop/New%20CSA/customersupport_AIagent/api/chargepoints.py)**, **[api/customer_data.py](file:///c:/Users/admin/Desktop/New%20CSA/customersupport_AIagent/api/customer_data.py)**, **[api/RemoteStart.py](file:///c:/Users/admin/Desktop/New%20CSA/customersupport_AIagent/api/RemoteStart.py)**, etc.: Formulate payload templates, submit HTTP POST/GET requests to ChargeMOD's backend endpoints, and handle response parsing.

